summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of Thirty-seventh Avenue South from south margin of Hanford Street to south margin of Coush Street in the City of Seattle, by grading and curbing under Ordinance No. 17453 creating Local Improvement District No. 1651 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
